  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A key hemolysis-index requirement mandates experimental-validation as the verification method; however, the supporting validation activity was conducted as a high-fidelity numerical simulation whose results were argued to be equivalent to bench-top experimental data. The package narrative presents the simulation as a credible surrogate for the required experiment, but the structured activityType field records 'numerical-simulation', directly contradicting the requirement's requiredVerificationMethod of 'experimental-validation'. Decision recorded as Accepted.",
